This paper deals with the concept of Age of Information (AoI) in a queueing system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the transmission of messages and the handling of a sequence of arrivals, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a variation of traditional AoI, which involves the use of relative AoI, a concept that can be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
